item.title: About Us
item.dc:creator: Andrew
item.content:encoded:
The University of Washington can be an intimidating experience for the new comer. You are immersed within a brand new community with brand new challenges and people to meet. With so much around you, its only natural to feel overwhelmed or a little lost especially without the familiar faces you may have had in high school. One thing you will notice around campus is the sense of belonging present in fraternity men. ZBT has a brotherhood of men who all can call our house their home and our members their brothers. Fraternity brothers are there for each other to celebrate each others successes and to pick each other up by the boot straps.
But, what can a fraternity offer you? Fraternities offer the opportunity to develop into a gentlemen and outstanding member of the community.
LEADERSHIP Fraternal living is an education in itself. Each chapter has a responsibility of services to its members, the college and the community. It is well known that fraternity members enjoy a much higher level of involvement in campus and community life than non-fraternity members. For this reason there are more than enough challenges to keep every member active in the daily operations of the chapter. Whether it is organizing a winning intramural team, balancing the chapter books, or helping a brother with his homework, all the jobs are important to the chapter. In addition they help you develop leadership skills through experiences. Zeta Beta Tau promotes new brother education programs designed to help new members develop their own leadership potential and adopt effective academic habits. Zeta Beta Tau realizes the importance of leadership development and annually hosts a nationwide leadership school and conclaves are held throughout the country to provide even more brothers with leadership experience.
BROTHERHOOD Brotherhood is what makes a fraternity important. The very word itself is important, the members of Zeta Beta Tau are not friends, they are brothers. Why are they brothers? Because we are there for each other now, when we are 20, and when we are 120. Being a brother is what makes ZBT relevant, and what makes men devote their lives to their fraternity. As part of building a brotherhood we have various brotherhood building events including pick-up basketball, intramural sports, office chair Mario Kart, and Formal. Joining the brotherhood of ZBT allows you to join something larger than yourself. When you join ZBT you join over 110,000 men who all share our brotherhood.
SCHOLARSHIP Fraternities offer a great way to better yourself academically. You go college to graduate and get a job, fraternities are built to help you do this. Nationally, fraternity members acquire grade point averages above all other college men’s scholastic rankings. In addition, 71% of all fraternity men graduate, while only 50% of non fraternity men graduate from college. Our chapter can help you academically with test banks, tutoring from older brothers in your major or classes, as well as rewards such as Dean’s List dinners. Not only do we prepare you succeed academically; fraternities also prepare you for the rest of your life. Since 1825 all but two U.S. presidents have been in a fraternity, 63% of the U.S. president’s cabinet members have been in a fraternity, as well as 76% of congress.
SOCIAL LIFE Your college experience would not be complete if you never stepped outside of the classroom or your dorm room. While the purpose of college remains scholastic, a social life is equally important in your college experience. We keep our social calendar busy with exchanges with sororities, philanthropy events, and more. The social life available to fraternity men teaches them confidence, manners, personality and social etiquette. A college career without the social life offered through a fraternity is simply not complete. Besides teaching important lessons, the social experience will provide you with the longest lasting memories of your college career. You will not always remember what was on that test a month ago, but you will always remember the fun times spent with your brothers.

item.title: Main Page
item.dc:creator: Andrew
item.content:encoded:
Zeta Beta Tau

Alpha Mu Chapter at University of Washington

Who We Are

Zeta Beta Tau was founded on December 29th, 1898. The mission of Zeta Beta Tau Fraternity is to foster and develop in its membership the tenets of its Credo: Intellectual Awareness, Social Responsibility, Integrity and Brotherly Love, in order to prepare its members for positions of leadership and service within their communities.The Alpha Mu chapter was re-founded in 2007 and strives to adhere to these principles by providing leadership positions, social events, philanthropic involvement, athletics and brotherhood development for our members. Fraternity can be one of the best choices to jump start your college experience and growth into adulthood. Come check us out, its a once and a lifetime experience. Rush ZBT

Intellectual Awareness

Fraternity creates an atmosphere conducive to the expansion of the individual's intellectual horizons, the interchange of ideas within the academic community and the pursuit of scholastic excellence. Zeta Beta Tau seeks to support this environment in anyway possible. By using the resources our house has at their disposal, our members can create an individual academic plan designed to ensure academic success.

Social Responsibility

Fraternity requires the individual to commit himself and accept his responsibility to participate. Zeta Beta Tau uses every available opportunity to educate undergraduate members on holding safe and legal social events. Additionally, Zeta Beta Tau strives to be a positive force within the community by volunteering at homeless shelters, raising money for charity, and more.

Integrity

Fraternity generates a standard of personal integrity – a framework for the individual to maintain honesty, exhibit loyalty and retain a sense of self-discipline. Zeta Beta Tau holds its members to rigorous standards called "Brotherhood Minimum Standards." These standards are the bare minimum for being a brother of Zeta Beta Tau, if a brother is having trouble reaching these standards, the house is their to pick them back up.

Brotherly Love

Fraternity inspires and expresses the interrelation of the individual with his fellows, his pride in the institution and respect for the wisdom of its tradition. Brotherhood is one of the most important aspects of Zeta Beta Tau. During their time in the house, Zeta Beta Tau members develop life long friendships not only with their brothers but with the community at large.

A Blog Post, YEAH

item.title: Parents
item.dc:creator: Andrew
item.content:encoded:
Why Choose ZBT as your place of living?

Living at ZBT comes with more than just a place to live. It comes with an opportunity to grow as a mature member of society. ZBT members attempt to better themselves everyday by living out the four pillars of which our house was established under: Intellectual Awareness, Social Responsibility, Integrity, & Brotherly Love. By living out our credo we not only improve the community around us but improve ourselves in the process.

How much does it cost?

ZBT, 2850 per quarter. Includes, room & board, philanthropy, social, 3 meals a day M - F(pro chef) - Chart comparison.

How does Zeta Beta Tau interact with its community?

We are constantly planning activities with other members of the Greek Community. Some of these events are in a more social context and can include fun activities such as BBQ’s or scavenger hunts While others are more philanthropic in nature and are set-up as a way to help either the community or a charity. By working closely with other members of the Greek System we not only create a friendly environment for friendships to form but also help make our community a better place.

Will Fraternity Life get in the way of academics?

Academics are the most important aspect of college, fraternity life is an extension of college and therefore it is also the most important aspect for ZBT also. ZBT wishes for all of its members to excel in their academics and as such we have many resources and systems that our members can take advantage of. One such system is our weekly study tables, these are scheduled times in which we have many of our members of the house study together. Having our members study together is advantous as many brothers have the same classes as each other and can help each other in the class. ZBT also has strict academic requirements for being an active brother. If at any time a brother’s GPA is lower than a 2.7 for two consecutive quarters than they will be removed from ZBT. Fortunately, ZBT has never had to act upon this policy partially because of the role the academics chairmen plays in ensuring that ZBT is a pro-academia environment. The academics chair’s responsibility is to ensure that all of the brothers of ZBT are reaching their full potential and will even help brothers in need by creating a personal plan with them to reach that potential.

What responsibilities do members of ZBT have?

Members of Zeta Beta Tau have many various responsibilities, however it generally depends on how much they wish to take on. At the bare minimum, brothers are required to attend Chapter(a weekly meeting that sums up the state of our house and how we want to continue to improve it) and do their chores. However, if a brother wishes to contribute more to the house and take on more responsibilities they can potentially take on a chairmen position and contribute to the house in that manner. Chairmen positions include: house manager, technology chairmen, academics chairmen, Risk manager, etc.

Hazing? Is that a thing? What about Pledging?

ZBT has a national no hazing policy that this chapter strictly adheres to. In addition, the UW Interfraternity Council also has a strict no hazing policy. People who sign with Zeta Beta Tau are considered members the moment they sign up, in an effort to educate new members on how to be productive brothers and to have them gradually get to know the house better we have put in place a Brotherhood Development Program which educates members on about what being a ZBT member is really about and how they can contribute.

How will Fraternity membership provide social activities for my student?

Zeta Beta Tau has strict policies regarding open events and underage drinking. We take great care to ensure that Zeta Beta Tau is a safe environment for everyone at all times. Zeta Beta Tau has many opportunities for brothers to educate themselves on how to hold safe and legal social events.

How Does Zeta Beta Tau make the world a better place

Zeta Beta Tau loves supporting its communities. One of the ways ZBT does this is through our annual philanthropy event, Get on the Ball. Every year we hit Red Square with a gigantic ball and have as many people sign a gigantic ball, based on the amount of signatures we get our sponsors will donate money based on that. Its a fun way to raise money for charity! In addition to our philanthropy event we also participate in many of the other Greek Communities philanthropy events. Last year we participated in AlphaPhifa, Alpha Phi’s philanthropy event, along with many other events. These events our only the ways that ZBT as an organization helps out the community. Members also volunteer and contribute to the community on an individual basis. We have brothers who help at the homeless shelter and tutor children as well.

Can I visit my Son?

Of course you can! We even have scheduled events for our beloved parents as well, we recognize that parents are perhaps our biggest supporters and we want to show our appreciation. Additionally, there is also a ZBT Parents club if you wish to be involved in that way as well. We have also had many parents contribute to the house as well!

How Can I Help Out?

If you would like to donate your time to Zeta Beta Tau, please use the contact button on the footer of this page and we will contact you back as soon as possible. If you wish to help, ZBT out financially there is also a donate button at the bottom of this page too.

item.title: Alumni
item.dc:creator: Andrew
item.content:encoded:
Fraternity extends beyond graduation, the Alpha Mu chapter extends an open invitation to all Zeta Beta Tau alumni in the northwest to connect or reconnect with us. We frequently hold events that extend to our alumni, including poker nights, alumni dinners, BBQs, and tailgate specifically for our Alumni. If you would like to be updated on when these events occur, sign up for the alumni newsletter and keep up to date with our chapter events.
